{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"254820ee-75da-4e1d-92c7-ba270b4d5ce8","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by reordering:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_IiAsv6bVyDuNeqY9Zgbeab","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-729fa228e315445aab4b9278c70407c5/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-729fa228e315445aab4b9278c70407c5/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"e4d53171-ff52-473b-84f9-28b7840e2a74","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, meaning it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compile order, `Services.fs` can't see the types defined in `Domain.fs`.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs` first, since it defines the types with no dependencies on other project files\n2. `Services.fs` next, which depends on Domain\n3. `Program.fs` last, since it depends on both Domain and Services","outputTokens":493,"requestId":"0426:11233D:CC5702:EA5148:69F2A778"},"id":"d0c4b8f4-6ac7-4787-9173-33c6f364a93f","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:12.710Z","parentId":"000